abstract:
The purpose of this study is to empirically study: (1) The effect of internal auditor competence on effectivity of internal audit function; (2) The effect of internal auditor objectivity on effectivity of internal audit function.   
This research uses survey method with description verification approach and type of causal research, conducted on 42 Inspectorat Local Government  in Java Island  as the unit of analysis, while the unit of  observation is a  Team Audit such as, Inspector, Inspector of area, audit team leader and members of audit team. The type  of data is  primary data collected by a questionnaire research instruments.   
The result of this study using multiple regression analysis finds that: (1) the internal auditor competence  affect the effectivity of internal audit function; (2) the internal auditor objectivity affect the effectivity of internal audit function;
